    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/1793: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 24, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Your telegram No. 54, April 23, 4 p.m. Assuming that the Protocol and
                    Convention will be signed today the Department will give out for publication in
                    Wednesday morning newspapers a statement synthesizing enclosure to its
                    instruction No. 323 and announcement suggested by Dr. Puig.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d461fn1">For text of press release issued by the Department of
                        State, April 24, 1934, see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press
                            Releases</hi>, April 28, 1934, p. 224.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
